@@TJvStatusBar
<TITLEIMG TJvStatusBar>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Bars.Statusbars
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Supports extended features such as hot tracking, and accepts controls dropped on it at design time.
Description
  TJvStatusBar is a TStatusBar ancestor that supports extended features such as hot tracking, and
  accepts controls dropped on it at design time.

  Use a TJvStatusBar if you want a status bar that enables hot tracking, or where you can place
  controls on.

  You can use OnMouseEnter and OnMouseLeave to alter the status bar's look or behavoir, when the user
  moves the mouse pointer over the control.

  Property HintColor can be used to set a different color of the Help hint boxes for the status bar.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvStatusBar.AutoHintShown
Summary
  Specifies whether the status bar is showing the current hint.
Description
  Read AutoHintShown to determine whether the status bar is showing the current hint.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvStatusBar.HintColor
Summary
  Determines the color of the hint boxes for the Help Hints for the status bar.
Description
  Use HintColor to specify the hint box color. A default color value of clInfoBk is set for the
  HintColor property in the constructor when the application is created. To change the HintColor
  assign it a new TColor value.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvStatusBar.OnParentColorChange
Summary
  Occurs when the color property for the parent of the status bar changes.
Description
  Write an OnParentColorChange event to take specific action when the ParentColor property changes.

